sources.leaves:
5-12 cm x 1.5-6; deciduous; leathery; flat; pinnatilobed; 
          base attenuate or sometimes rounded, often asymmetrical; margin with 
          regular, narrow lobes and sinuses; sinuses reaching the 1/3 of half-blade; 
          lobes often lobulate; young leaves densely whitish 
          tomentose both sides; adult leaves adaxially green, lustrous, with some 
          stellate trichomes, glabrescent; abaxially densely greyish tomentose, 
          with stellate, fasciculate and simples hairs; 9-10 secondary parallel 
          veins pairs, with intercalary veins near the base; petiole pinkish, 
          7-16 mm long, stellate pubescent;

