sources.leaves:
5.5-15 cm x 3-5; oval or oboval-oblong; 
        apex rounded or shortly acute; base attenuate or rounded; margin remotely 
        dentate near apex, entire or sinuate near base; young leaves densely pubescent 
        both sides; mature leaves hairless; glaucous beneath with abundant wax; 
        midrib slightly impressed adaxially, prominent below; 9-10 vein pairs 
        impressed above, prominent below; petiole 1-3 cm, initially densely yellowish 
        pubescent, then glabrous;

5-8 x 1.5-3 
        cm; narrowly elliptic to elliptic ; slightly leathery; apex acuminate; 
        base cuneate; margin serrulate towards apical 1/2; green above; bloomy, 
        whitish beneath; 8-10 vein pairs, thin, evident beneath, at an angle of 
        35° with midrib; petiole pubescent, 5-10 mm long;

(6-)8-11(-15) cm x 3-4,5(-5); leathery; oblong-elliptical 
          or oboval; apex acuminate, acumen up to 0.6 cm long; base cuneate; margin 
          recurved, serrulate in the 1/5-1/7 apical part; both sides hairless; 
          light green underneath; midrib nearly flat adaxially, prominent abaxially 
          as are the lateral veins; 8-11 vein pairs, at an angle of 40-45° 
          with the midrib, straight; tertiary veins scalariform, evident abaxially; 
          petiole 1-2 cm long, glabrous;

